    "statement": {
      "informal": "Natural logarithm is a single F16 node via the extended EXL operator: EXL(0, x) = exp(0) · log x = 1 · log x = log x. Trivially-named but pedagogically important — it shows that ln gets its 1n cost via a multiplicative-identity exploitation rather than an exp/log cancellation.",
